I watched as the Ibaras looked back and forth reluctantly as they departed, then I began to get ready.

...I'm going on a journey.

If we stay here forever, maybe we'll meet again in ten or twenty years, when the elven barrier weakens.

However, if this allows humans to get close to this place, the elves will be put at risk.

If my being here only strengthens the bond between humans and elves, then perhaps I should leave this land as well.

I feel bad for the books that were left here, but I can't take everything with me so I give up.

I also put the things I had written down together in one book.

With a faint hope that it will be of use to anyone who ever decides to live in the hut again.

The villagers might sell it off before then, but I'd be happy if someone who could put it to good use picked it up.

Ibara, Hinata, Konomi, Tsukiyo, it was fun.

I also had a lot of fun spending time with everyone.

