After walking for a while, as expected, I came across some villagers.

They are carrying nets, ropes, and weapons, and are fully prepared to capture the elves.


[Villager 1] "Hey! You bastard! What are you doing here?!"

It seemed they had already done some groundwork, as the villagers surrounded me with murderous intent.

They must have been told that I had outwitted everyone and had the elf all to myself or something.

I quickly pointed at the general store owner's son and yelled.

"You're the reason the elves ran away!"


[Villager 2] "Huh?"

The guys surrounding me all turned to look at the general store owner's son.


[Villager 1] "Eh...? What are you talking about... That's not true! That's not true!"

The more I panicked and tried to make an excuse, the more stern the gazes from everyone became.

"We'll never catch another elf, you thief has caused so much damage to the village!"

When I emphasized that it was a huge loss for the village, the hostility directed towards me was now directed towards the general store owner.


[Villager 2] "Now that I think about it, it was him who suggested we take anything valuable because the house was vacant."


[Villager 3] "...Now that I think about it, things have disappeared from my house before too. Maybe..."


[Villager 1] "No! No! That's not me!"


[Villager 4] "So does that mean there's something else you can think of?"

...Perhaps he was also feeling some resentment towards the general store owner's son because of his arrogance.

The villagers' illusion that they could make a lot of money by capturing and selling elves was shattered, and their anger was directed at the general store owner's son who had been leading the way.

